reviews.review: It was good and pretty much what I expected.  The plot twist was interesting.

Now that I've seen it, I'll go back and read all the reviews to find out what the critics didn't like about this movie. I thought it was a lot of fun and tied up loose ends. It is a very busy movie, for sure - anybody who has issues with motion should sit far away from the screen. The only thing that didn't completely work for me was how they dealt with adding Carrie Fisher - the CGI was a bit stiff and awkward.
I have absolutely no idea what the critics have against this movie. This is one of the best Star Wars films I've ever seen and a brilliant ending to an incredible saga.
Donâ€™t listen to the critics. This was a great installment in the series and the ending was the best possible one. Watch it and see for yourselves
This is one movie that no one can "fix in post", no matter the budget. Just plain awful, full of ridiculous contrivances, and not fun.

Good ending to the sequel Imaginative ways to bring back key characters from the original Star wars trilogy.  If this is the last in the seris, it was a great way to finish, but it left the door cracked open if it were to continue.  Especially liked seeing Harrison Ford cameo.

The plot was extremely confused the audience being whisked between locations without leaving any time to process events, which made the movie feel unsatisfying to watch. The way the finale was executed also suffered from this, although the problem here may more with what was going on, with characters doing what can only be described as intensely stupid, or completely unexpected things which just served to ruin the immersion, although it did provide some involuntary humour. There also weren't any especially amazing pieces of cinematography or choreography in the movie, which was somewhat disappointing considering the track record so far. In the context of being a Star Wars movie this overall added up to make a deeply dissatisfying experience which made me wish I hadn't watched it.
Trite dialogue, wooden acting, absolutely predictable (and dull) plot.  Both my eight and eleven year old kids said "we should have seen Jumanji instead."

Total jumbled up mess, got me lost as soon as it began as I don't recall the previous episode's story, just couldn't follow throughout the whole movie! This last trilogy lacks a good plot and star power, should have just stopped after Ep.3 which was already terrible. Thank heavens it's all over.
